================================================================================
SECTION A: INITIAL CONFIGURATION (PARAMETERS & SETUP)
================================================================================

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
A.1 WAREHOUSE MANAGEMENT PARAMETERS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Navigation: Warehouse management > Setup > Warehouse management parameters

The Warehouse management parameters page is the central configuration hub for
enabling and controlling warehouse processes across the organization.

KEY PARAMETER TABS:

1. GENERAL TAB
   -----------
   - Work FastTab
     * General warehouse work policies
     * Default work priority values
     * Deferred work processing settings
     * Work transaction dates
     * Default work class ID
   
   - Location Types FastTab
     * Staging location type (mandatory)
     * Final shipping location type (mandatory)
     * Default receiving location

2. LOADS TAB
   ----------
   - Load packing slip processing
   - Capture receiving completed packing slip settings
   - Load building parameters
   - Auto-load creation on order release

3. WAVE PROCESSING TAB
   --------------------
   - Wave processing batch group
   - Process waves in batch (Yes/No)
   - Wait for lock (milliseconds)
   - Automate wave creation
   - Automate replenishment work release

4. CYCLE COUNTING TAB
   -------------------
   - Default cycle counting adjustment type: Cycle Count
   - Default cycle counting work class ID
   - Default cycle count work priority (e.g., 50)

5. NUMBER SEQUENCES TAB
   ---------------------
   - Wave ID
   - Work ID
   - Container ID
   - Shipment ID
   - Load ID
   - License plate ID
   - Inbound shipment order (for WMS Only Mode)
   - Outbound shipment order (for WMS Only Mode)

6. MOBILE DEVICE TAB
   ------------------
   - Display tracking dimension control settings
   - Inventory dimension display options
   - Mobile app global parameters

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
A.2 WAREHOUSE SETUP
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Navigation: Warehouse management > Setup > Warehouse > Warehouses

PREREQUISITE CONFIGURATIONS:

1. Sites
   - Each warehouse must be associated with a site
   - Site controls legal entity and tax configuration
   
2. Warehouse Types
   - Default: Main warehouse for normal operations
   - Quarantine: For quarantine-controlled items
   - Transit: For transfer orders and delivery date control

WAREHOUSE CONFIGURATION:

Key Fields:
- Use warehouse management processes: YES (enables WMS)
- Default receipt location (receiving dock)
- Default issue location
- Master planning warehouse
- Inventory aisle template

Enable Warehouse Management Processes:
Navigation: Warehouse management > Setup > Enable warehouse management processes 
           > Change storage dimension group for items

Requirements for enabling WMS:
1. Create new inventory status value (set as default in parameters)
2. Create new storage dimension group with "Use warehouse management processes" = Yes
3. Define new reservation hierarchy
4. Create unit sequence groups
5. Run "Change storage dimension group for items" job

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
A.3 STORAGE DIMENSION GROUPS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Navigation: Product information management > Setup > Dimension and variant groups
           > Storage dimension groups

STANDARD STORAGE DIMENSIONS:
- Site (mandatory for WMS)
- Warehouse (mandatory for WMS)
- Inventory status (optional but recommended)
- Location (below warehouse - WMS controlled)
- License plate (lowest level - WMS controlled)

CONFIGURATION OPTIONS:
- Use warehouse management processes: YES
- Active dimensions
- Physical inventory
- Financial inventory
- Coverage plan by dimension

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
A.4 RESERVATION HIERARCHIES
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Navigation: Warehouse management > Setup > Inventory > Reservation hierarchies

PURPOSE: Defines the order in which inventory dimensions are reserved

STANDARD HIERARCHY LEVELS (example):
Level 1: Site (lowest - least specific)
Level 2: Warehouse
Level 3: Inventory status
Level 4: Location
Level 5: License plate (highest - most specific)

HIERARCHY TYPES:
- Batch-above: Batch number above location (reserve specific batch at order entry)
- Batch-below: Batch number below location (batch determined during picking)

KEY SETTING:
- Allow reservation on demand order: Enables flexible batch reservation

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
A.5 LOCATION SETUP
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

A.5.1 Zone Groups
Navigation: Warehouse management > Setup > Warehouse > Zone groups
- Logical grouping of zones (e.g., Bulk, Pick, Staging)

A.5.2 Zones
Navigation: Warehouse management > Setup > Warehouse > Zones
- Assigned to zone groups
- Used in location directive queries

A.5.3 Location Types
Navigation: Warehouse management > Setup > Warehouse > Location types
- Staging
- Pack
- Baydoor
- Bulk
- Pick
- Receive

A.5.4 Location Profiles
Navigation: Warehouse management > Setup > Warehouse > Location profiles

Key Settings:
- Use license plate tracking: Yes/No
- Allow mixed items: Yes/No
- Allow mixed inventory batches: Yes/No
- Allow mixed inventory statuses: Yes/No
- Allow negative inventory: Yes/No
- Allow cycle counting: Yes/No
- Location stocking limits (optional)

A.5.5 Location Formats
Navigation: Warehouse management > Setup > Warehouse > Location formats
- Defines naming convention for locations
- Segments: Aisle, Rack, Shelf, Bin

A.5.6 Location Setup Wizard
Navigation: Warehouse management > Setup > Warehouse > Location setup wizard
- Automates bulk location creation
- Uses location formats for naming

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
A.6 INVENTORY STATUSES
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Navigation: Warehouse management > Setup > Inventory > Inventory statuses

CONFIGURATION FIELDS:
- Inventory status ID
- Name
- Inventory blocking: Yes/No
  * YES = Creates blocking reservation, excluded from MRP
  * NO = Available but segregated by status dimension

COMMON STATUSES:
- Available (default for normal operations)
- Blocked
- Damaged
- QA Hold
- Quarantine
- Reserved

DEFAULT STATUS ASSIGNMENT:
- Site level
- Warehouse level  
- Item level
- Purchase order/Sales order/Transfer order level

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
A.7 UNIT SEQUENCE GROUPS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Navigation: Product information management > Setup > Unit of measure 
           > Unit sequence groups

PURPOSE: Defines unit conversion sequences for warehouse processes

Example Sequence:
1. Each (ea)
2. Box
3. Case
4. Pallet

Required for:
- License plate receiving
- Mixed unit handling
- Catch weight processing


================================================================================
SECTION B: CORE BUSINESS LOGIC (STRUCTURES & RULES)
================================================================================

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
B.1 WAVE TEMPLATES
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Navigation: Warehouse management > Setup > Waves > Wave templates

WAVE TEMPLATE TYPES:
1. Shipping - Sales orders, transfer orders, outbound shipment orders
2. Production - Production orders
3. Kanban - Kanban orders

KEY CONFIGURATION FIELDS:

Header Settings:
- Wave template name
- Wave template description
- Site and Warehouse
- Sequence number (lower = higher priority)

Automation Settings:
- Automate wave creation: Yes/No
- Assign to open waves: Yes/No
- Process wave automatically at threshold: Yes/No
- Automate replenishment work release: Yes/No
- Continue wave processing when work creation fails: Yes/No

Threshold Settings:
- Wave weight threshold
- Shipment threshold
- Line threshold

WAVE PROCESS METHODS (sequence matters):
1. createWave - Creates wave
2. allocateWave - Allocates inventory
3. createWork - Creates warehouse work
4. buildLoads - Builds loads (optional)
5. containerize - Containerizes shipments (optional)
6. replenish - Creates replenishment work (optional)
7. print - Prints wave labels (optional)

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
B.2 WORK TEMPLATES
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Navigation: Warehouse management > Setup > Work > Work templates

WORK ORDER TYPES:
- Sales orders
- Purchase orders
- Production orders (put away, pick, finished goods)
- Transfer issues/receipts
- Inventory movement
- Cycle counting
- Replenishment
- Quality orders
- Kanban
- Inbound shipment orders (WMS Only Mode)
- Outbound shipment orders (WMS Only Mode)

WORK TEMPLATE STRUCTURE:

Header:
- Work template name
- Work order type
- Sequence number
- Valid from/to dates
- Site/Warehouse (optional filters)

Work Template Details (lines):
- Sequence number
- Work type: Pick, Put, Count, Custom
- Work class ID
- Directive code (links to location directive)
- Mandatory/Optional settings

Work Breaks:
- Work header breaks (creates new work ID)
- Location group fields
- Sorting fields

CRITICAL CONCEPTS:

Work Class:
- Groups work by type
- Links work templates to mobile menu items
- Controls which workers can process which work

Directive Code:
- Links work template line to specific location directive
- Enables granular picking/putting rules

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
B.3 LOCATION DIRECTIVES
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Navigation: Warehouse management > Setup > Location directives

WORK ORDER TYPES:
- Sales orders (Pick and Put)
- Purchase orders (Put)
- Transfer orders (Pick and Put)
- Production orders (Various)
- Replenishment
- And more...

LOCATION DIRECTIVE STRUCTURE:

Header:
- Name
- Work order type
- Work type (Pick or Put)
- Site
- Warehouse
- Directive code (optional - links to work template)
- Sequence number
- Multiple SKU: Yes/No

Lines (query filters):
- Sequence number
- From quantity / To quantity
- Unit
- Locate quantity: Picking quantity, Available quantity, All
- Restrict by unit: Yes/No

Actions:
- Name
- Sequence number
- Strategy (see below)
- Fixed location usage
- Allow negative inventory: Yes/No
- Query (defines location criteria)

LOCATION DIRECTIVE STRATEGIES:

For PICK:
- None (use query only)
- Match packing quantity
- Consolidate
- FEFO batch reservation
- Round up to full LP

For PUT:
- None (use query only)
- Empty location with no incoming work
- Consolidate

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
B.4 WORK POOLS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Navigation: Warehouse management > Setup > Work > Work pools

PURPOSE:
- Organize work into groups
- Classify work by location, priority, or type
- Used for workload balancing

ASSIGNMENT:
- Assigned to work templates (most work types)
- Assigned to cycle counting plans/thresholds

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
B.5 MOBILE DEVICE CONFIGURATION
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

B.5.1 Workers
Navigation: Warehouse management > Setup > Worker

Configuration:
- Link to employee record
- Default user ID
- Default menu assignment
- Warehouse assignments
- Work user ID and password

B.5.2 Mobile Device Users
Navigation: Warehouse management > Setup > Mobile device > Mobile device users

Configuration:
- User ID
- Password
- Default warehouse
- Assigned menu
- Work user privileges

Supervisor Settings:
- Cycle count supervisor: Yes/No
- Adjustment quantity limits

B.5.3 Mobile Device Menu Items
Navigation: Warehouse management > Setup > Mobile device > Mobile device menu items

MENU ITEM MODES:
1. Indirect - Activities/inquiries (no work creation)
2. Work - Creates or processes work

WORK CREATION PROCESSES:
- Purchase order item receiving
- Purchase order item receiving (and putaway)
- Mixed license plate receiving
- License plate receiving
- Load item receiving
- Sales order picking
- Transfer issue
- Production put away
- Cycle counting
- Movement
- Status change
- And many more...

KEY SETTINGS:
- Display settings (customize prompts)
- Work confirmation requirements
- Default data fields
- Barcode data policy
- Generate license plate: Yes/No
- Use process guide: Yes/No

B.5.4 Mobile Device Menus
Navigation: Warehouse management > Setup > Mobile device > Mobile device menus

Structure:
- Menu name
- Menu structure (menu items and submenus)
- Hierarchy organization

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
B.6 CONTAINER TYPES AND PACKING
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

B.6.1 Container Types
Navigation: Warehouse management > Setup > Containers > Container types

Configuration:
- Container type ID
- Description
- Tare weight
- Maximum weight
- Maximum volume
- Length, Width, Height

B.6.2 Container Groups
Navigation: Warehouse management > Setup > Containers > Container groups

B.6.3 Packing Profiles
Navigation: Warehouse management > Setup > Packing > Packing profiles

Settings:
- Container closing policy
- Container release policy
- Manifest at container close
- Print packing slip

B.6.4 Packing Station Setup
Navigation: Warehouse management > Setup > Packing > Packing station setup

Configuration:
- Warehouse
- Location (packing location)
- Create packing work: Yes/No


================================================================================
SECTION C: OPERATIONAL PROCESSES (DAILY & PERIODIC TRANSACTIONS)
================================================================================

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
C.1 INBOUND PROCESSES
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

C.1.1 Purchase Order Receiving Flow

Standard Process Flow:
1. Purchase order creation
2. Purchase order confirmation
3. Load planning (optional)
4. Arrival overview registration (optional)
5. Mobile device receiving
   - Scan PO number or load
   - Scan item/license plate
   - Register quantity
6. Putaway work execution
7. Purchase order product receipt

Mobile Device Menu Items for Receiving:
- Purchase order item receiving (registration only)
- Purchase order item receiving (and putaway)
- Load item receiving
- Mixed license plate receiving

Key Parameters:
- Load over receipt settings
- License plate grouping policy
- Allow mixed items/batches/statuses

C.1.2 Inbound Load Handling

Load Creation:
- Manual creation
- Automatic from purchase orders
- From ASN (Advanced Shipment Notice)

Load Processing:
1. Load scheduling
2. Appointment scheduling (optional)
3. Load arrival (registration)
4. Receiving via mobile device
5. Receiving completed confirmation
6. Putaway work completion

C.1.3 Transfer Receipt

Process:
1. Transfer order shipment (from source warehouse)
2. Transit processing
3. Receiving at destination warehouse
4. Putaway work execution

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
C.2 OUTBOUND PROCESSES
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

C.2.1 Sales Order Picking Flow

Standard Process Flow:
1. Sales order creation
2. Inventory reservation
3. Release to warehouse
4. Wave creation and processing
5. Work creation (picking work)
6. Mobile device picking execution
7. Staging (if applicable)
8. Packing (if applicable)
9. Load building
10. Shipment confirmation
11. Packing slip posting

Release to Warehouse Options:
- Direct from sales order
- Release sales orders to warehouse (batch)
- From load planning workbench
- Automatic via wave template

C.2.2 Wave Processing

Automatic Wave Processing:
- Triggered on release to warehouse (if configured)
- Batch job processing (wave processing batch group)

Manual Wave Processing:
Navigation: Warehouse management > Outbound waves > Shipment waves
- Select wave
- Process wave button

Wave Processing Steps:
1. createWave - Creates wave record
2. allocateWave - Reserves inventory
3. createWork - Generates picking work
4. buildLoads - Creates/updates loads
5. containerize - Auto-containerization (optional)
6. replenish - Replenishment work (optional)
7. print - Label printing (optional)

C.2.3 Picking Execution

Mobile Device Picking:
1. Select Sales Picking menu item
2. Enter work ID or scan license plate
3. Navigate to pick location
4. Confirm pick (item, quantity, LP)
5. Navigate to put location (staging/pack/baydoor)
6. Confirm put

Picking Strategies:
- System-directed: System determines pick sequence
- User-directed: Worker determines sequence
- Cluster picking: Multiple orders picked simultaneously

C.2.4 Packing Process

Manual Packing (Pack Station):
Navigation: Warehouse management > Packing and containerization > Pack

Process:
1. Select packing station and profile
2. Scan shipment ID or license plate
3. Create container
4. Scan items into container
5. Close container
6. Print labels/manifest

Automatic Containerization:
- Configured via wave template
- Container build templates define logic

C.2.5 Shipment Confirmation

Navigation: Warehouse management > Loads > All loads

Process:
1. Complete all picking work
2. Complete packing (if applicable)
3. Confirm outbound shipment
4. System updates:
   - Load status: Shipped
   - Triggers packing slip posting (queued)

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
C.3 INVENTORY MANAGEMENT PROCESSES
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

C.3.1 Cycle Counting

Types of Cycle Counting:
1. Threshold-based (automatic when below quantity)
2. Plan-based (scheduled intervals)
3. Spot counting (ad-hoc via mobile)
4. System-directed (work creation)
5. User-directed

Cycle Counting Plan:
Navigation: Warehouse management > Setup > Cycle counting > Cycle count plans

Settings:
- Warehouse
- Location selection query
- Maximum cycle counts
- Days between cycle counts
- Work pool

Cycle Count Threshold:
Navigation: Warehouse management > Setup > Cycle counting > Cycle count thresholds

Settings:
- Item/Item group
- Warehouse
- Minimum quantity threshold
- Percentage threshold

Process Flow:
1. System creates cycle count work
2. Worker receives work via mobile device
3. Worker counts physical inventory
4. Worker enters counted quantity
5. System compares to expected
6. Variance handling (approval if needed)
7. Inventory adjustment posting

Variance Approval:
Navigation: Warehouse management > Cycle counting > Cycle count work pending review

C.3.2 Inventory Adjustments

Adjustment Types:
1. Counting journal (cycle count variance)
2. Adjustment journal (manual adjustment)
3. Movement journal (location transfers)
4. Transfer journal (warehouse transfers)

Mobile Device Adjustments:
- Adjustment in
- Adjustment out
- Movement (location to location)
- Status change

Reason Codes:
Navigation: Warehouse management > Setup > Reason codes

C.3.3 Inventory Status Change

Periodic Process:
Navigation: Warehouse management > Periodic tasks > Inventory status change

Purpose: Bulk status changes based on criteria (e.g., location-based blocking)

C.3.4 Inventory Blocking

Types:
1. Manual blocking (Inventory blocking page)
2. Quality order blocking
3. Inventory status blocking

Navigation: Inventory management > Periodic tasks > Inventory blocking

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
C.4 REPLENISHMENT
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Replenishment Types:

1. Min/Max Replenishment
   - Triggered when location falls below minimum
   - Replenishes up to maximum quantity

2. Wave Demand Replenishment
   - Triggered during wave processing
   - Fulfills immediate picking demand

3. Fixed Location Replenishment
   - Maintains inventory at fixed picking locations

Configuration:
Navigation: Warehouse management > Setup > Replenishment > Replenishment templates

Key Settings:
- Replenishment type (Min/Max, Wave demand, Fixed)
- Source location directive
- Destination location criteria
- Quantity unit and limits
- Wave step code (for wave demand)

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
C.5 CROSS-DOCKING
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Types:
1. Planned cross-docking (based on supply/demand matching)
2. Opportunistic cross-docking (real-time matching during receiving)

Configuration:
Navigation: Warehouse management > Setup > Work > Cross docking templates

Process Flow:
1. Inbound receipt registration
2. System identifies matching outbound demand
3. Cross-dock work created
4. Items moved directly to staging/shipping
5. Bypass putaway to storage

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
C.6 PERIODIC TASKS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Navigation: Warehouse management > Periodic tasks

Key Periodic Jobs:

1. Release to warehouse
   - Batch processing of order releases

2. Process waves
   - Batch wave processing

3. Inventory status change
   - Bulk status updates

4. Clean up work lines
   - Removes completed work records

5. Load packing slip posting
   - Posts queued packing slips

6. Shipment statistics cleanup
   - Maintenance task

7. Message processor (WMS Only Mode)
   - Processes shipment order messages


================================================================================
